This paper discusses a method for automatically building and ranking paths between entities in a knowledge graph using learned embeddings. This involves using a knowledge base completion model, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it involves mining scientific literature to assemble the knowledge graph. Information retrieval (cs.IR) is also relevant as the paper discusses ranking paths based on their relevance. Finally, the paper involves working with a knowledge graph, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB).
